Package gw.plugin.web.multicluster

Interface IMultiClusterSessionPlugin

All Superinterfaces:
InternalPlugin, Remote
public interface IMultiClusterSessionPlugin extends InternalPlugin
Implement this plugin for multi cluster environments where unsaved work might be spread between different clusters and a special unsaved work service orchestrates an access to unsaved work items.

  • Method Details

    • getOrCreateSession

      IMultiClusterSession getOrCreateSession(User user, jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request)
      Called when a new local user session is created, returns an object representing the cross cluster unsaved work session. All subsequent calls to the plugin will provide the cross cluster unsaved work session as an argument so the plugin knows which user session the action corresponds to.
      Parameters:
      user - the user corresponding to the newly created local session
      request - the HTTP request that caused the new local user session to be created
      Returns:
      an opaque object representing the cross cluster unsaved work session

    • closeLocalSession

      void closeLocalSession(IMultiClusterSession session)
      Notify the plugin that the local session associated with the given multi cluster session and been close. Usually called when the user logs out or their session times out.
      Parameters:
      session - the unsaved work session

    • addLocalUnsavedWork

      void addLocalUnsavedWork(IMultiClusterSession session, String key, String title, long timeStamp, String groupKey, String groupTitle)
      Add a local unsaved work location to the unsaved work service. If the information for a piece of unsaved work changes this method may be called multiple times with the same key, without an intervening call to removeLocalUnsavedWork(IMultiClusterSession, String). In such a case the updated information should overwrite any existing information for the key.
      Parameters:
      session - the session which has the unsaved work
      key - a string key that uniquely identifies the unsaved work within this user's session on this host
      title - the user readable title of the unsaved work, to be displayed in the UI
      timeStamp - a UTC time (milliseconds since Jan 1st 1970) indicating when the work was last accessed
      groupKey - the local string key that identifies this unsaved work's group, or null if there is none
      groupTitle - the user readable title for this unsaved work's group, or null if there is none

    • removeLocalUnsavedWork

      void removeLocalUnsavedWork(IMultiClusterSession session, String key)
      Remove a local unsaved work location from the unsaved work service
      Parameters:
      session - the session which has the unsaved work
      key - a string key that uniquely identifies the unsaved work within this user's session on this host

    • getRemoteUnsavedWork

      Set<IRemoteUnsavedWork> getRemoteUnsavedWork(IMultiClusterSession session)
      Get all the unsaved work from other clusters; must not include any local work

    • goToRemoteWork

      void goToRemoteWork(IMultiClusterSession session, IRemoteUnsavedWork remoteWork, boolean goToGroup)
      Go to the UI displaying the given remote work. This will take the user to another cluster. If the goToGroup parameter is true then go to the parent location group of the remote work.

    • getRemoteKeepAliveUrls

      Set<String> getRemoteKeepAliveUrls(IMultiClusterSession session)
      Returns a set of urls that can be "pinged" to keep remote sessions alive. The URL returns a minimal image so a browser can GET this image without requiring CORS and fetching it will keep the remote session alive

    • leaveCluster

      void leaveCluster(IMultiClusterSession session, String url)
      Notification method, called when the local session executes a multi cluster navigation ExitPoint, signifying that we're about to redirect to another cluster. If the plugin implementation does any caching this may be a good time to sync with the remote server as any local changes should be published to the server before going to another cluster. Plugin implementations can also leave this method empty, no implementation is required.
      Parameters:
      session - the session which is moving to another cluster
      url - the exit point URL
